-- Sensitive Index Extends Gains From Record Close in Special Diwali Trading
-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-11-05T12:50:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/sensitive-index-extends-gains-from-record-close-in-special-diwali-trading.html
India’s benchmark stock index rose,
extending gains from a record close, as investors increased
their holdings in a shortened trading session amid expectations
the nation’s economic growth will boost corporate earnings.  The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
gained as much as 215.07, or 1 percent, to 21,108.64 in Mumbai.
The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange rose 0.9
percent to 6,325.55   Indian stock exchanges are holding a special truncated
trading session today until 7 p.m. to allow brokers and
investors to make token stock purchases during the one-hour
trading session on Diwali, the festival of light and the start
of the Hindu new year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
